<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>If 24 AA points to get Manaburn wasn't a sufficient argument, 48 AA isn't either, especially as AA are signficantly easier to get now.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
MC = 12, MB = 5.  That's not 24.  Don't count general skills by the way... they aren't counted towards the 48 the SKs need.  As I said in another thread, people had a big problem with how easy MB was to get, then hold Kunark content hostage.  You're kidding yourself if you don't think half the Wizards who were getting AA didn't go after MB as their first or second skill pre-nerf.  Many servers had literally 20 or more Wizard with the MB ability a couple of months after the expansion.  You'd be hard-pressed to find 20 SKs with this ability across 3 servers. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   Also, let's not forget that HT carries quite a bit of aggro and has a very, very short range.<br>
<br>
What needs to be done to improve Manaburn is very simple and has been suggested by many before.  First of all fix the broken crits.  Secondly, either lower the mana consumption to half or make it a recourse effect like the Necros have on their HP for Lifeburn.  There, MB is improved... not fixed, because it's not broken as a skill!<br>
